  • java.lang.Object
    • services.ServiceRecord

  • public class ServiceRecord
extends java.lang.Object

        This constructor creates a new ServiceRecord Object; all of the arguments are strings.
        Parameters:
        dateProvided - the date the service was provided
        dateRec - the current date
        timeRec - the current time
        memName - the name of the member
        memNum - the memberNumber
        provNum - the provider number
        servCode - the service code
        servFee - the service fee
        com - optional comments
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - thrown if memNum or provNum are less than or equal to 0
